By Chibuike Nwabuko Abuja (Sundiata Post) – President Muhammadu Buhari has fired Babatunde Fowler and appointed Muhammad Nami as the chairman of the Federal Inland Revenue Service. The statement from the presidency on Monday afternoon, announced Muhammad Nami, a tax consultant, as the new head of the revenue agency. The announcement came hours after the ten55292ure of Mr Fowler expired and no renewal was immediately announced. Mr Fowler was appointed in 2015. Details later….